* Motion Compensated Temporal Filtering *

* Compilation:

	user@host:~/MCTF/trunk$ ./compile

* Installation (in the MCTF's directory!):

	user@host:~/MCTF/trunk$ export MCTF=$PWD
	export PATH=$PATH:~/bin

* MCJ2K encoding/decoding:

	mkdir tmp
	cd tmp
	ln -s ~/videos/mobile_352x288x30x420x300.yuv low_0
	mcj2k compress
	mcj2k info
	mkdir tmp
	cp *.mjc *type* tmp
	cd tmp
	mcj2k expand
	mplayer low_0 -demuxer rawvideo -rawvideo cif -loop 0

** How I can control the number of encoded frames?:

	rm -f *motion*
	mcj2k compress --pictures=289
	mcj2k info --pictures=289
	mcj2k expand --pictures=289

** How I can define the number of quality layers?:

	mcj2k compress --slopes="44000,43500,43000 # Higher slopes,
	                                           # worst qualities
	mcj2k info
	mcj2k expand # 44000
	mcj2k expand --layers=2 # 43500
	mcj2k expand --layers=3 # 43000

** How I can specify the number of temporal resolution levels?:

	rm -f *motion*
	mcj2k compress --temporal_levels=6
	mcj2k info --temporal_levels=6
	mcj2k expand --temporal_levels=6

* MCJPG encoding/decoding:

	mkdir tmp
	cd tmp
	ln -s ~/videos/mobile_352x288x30x420x300.yuv low_0
	mcjpg compress
	mcjpg info
	mkdir tmp
	cp *.mjpeg *.mjc *type* tmp
	cd tmp
	mcjpg expand
	mplayer low_0 -demuxer rawvideo -rawvideo cif -loop 0

** How I can control the number of encoded frames?:

	rm -f *motion*
	mcjpg compress --pictures=289
	mcjpg info --pictures=289
	mcjpg expand --pictures=289

** How I can define the quality of the unique layer:

	mcjpg compress --slopes="25" # Higher slopes, worst qualities 
	mcjpg info
	mcjpg expand

** How I can specify the number of temporal resolution levels?:

	rm -f *motion*
	mcjpg compress --temporal_levels=6
	mcjpg info --temporal_levels=6
	mcjpg expand --temporal_levels=6
